    {
      "id": "2c35247f6099aca4b57bada5185ebef695a1d8f5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-09-13 10:19:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThis patch will miss cancelling child LOOKUP lock for unlink and rename operations.\n\nActually, the MF_MDC_CANCEL_FID* flags looks quite confusing to me, how about make the changes like:\n\n- replacing MF_MDC_CANCEL_FID* to MF_LOCAL_FID*, each MF_LOCAL_FID(n) indicating if the fid(n) is a local fid; \n- by default, the MDC_LOCAL_FID* are present in op_flags, and lmv is responsible for clearing the flags in lmv_early_cancel();\n- mdc operations (mdc_unlink, mdc_rename...) checks the MDC_LOCAL_FID* flags and decides if it should do sync cancel on some certain fid.\n\nIn a word, lmv should only tell mdc if the fid is local, and mdc decides if it should do sync cancel on the fid base on this information.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "e346209523196a22a79addc4b4575680ced5d820",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-09-13 10:24:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nminor fix to my previous comment:\n\nit's better to use MF_REMOTE_FID* flags instead of MF_LOCAL_FID* flags.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "9af3d596b869edc0a1970fcea0185dc6b4ac20d8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-13 15:51:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nHmm, unlink and rename may miss sync lock cancel in MDC, I will update the patch.\n\nAs for the flag name, I think current one is more straightforward, it just tells whether MDC should cancel locks synchronously in it's rpc to MDT.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "2d1a37a45085669b1597d6444453f842401e5af5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2011-09-13 15:52:05.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 4.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "8a3c9d262e660e44fb290bb24a90c66ac2eaf5e7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 2,
        "name": "Jenkins",
        "username": "hudson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-09-13 15:52:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nBuild Started http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/2180/ ",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "b5618acd9a0b8550cb9303d7deae9e8fcb172271",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-09-13 16:19:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThe current logic looks a little bit twisted:\n- We set all the MF_MDC_CANCEL_FID? in llite layer;\n- Then clear some flags in lmv layer; (if the corresponding fid is remote fid, and it's not the fid2 of unlink or rename)\n- Send sync cancel in mdc layer according to the MF_MDC_CANCEL_FID? flags;\n\nI think it can be simplified as:\n\n- Do nothing in llite layer;\n- Set MF_REMOTE_FID? in lmv layer; (if the corresponding fid is remote fid)\n- Send sync cancel in mdc layer according to the MF_REMOTE_FID? flags; (if the flag is not present or it's a _must_ sync cancel fid, for instance, fid2 of unlink or rename) \n\nThe MF_REMOTE_FID? flags can also be used for other purpose in the future.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
